.TH "pnut.toml" "5" "2026-04-08"
.P
.SH NAME
.P
pnut.\&toml - pnut sandbox configuration file
.P
.SH DESCRIPTION
.P
The \fBpnut\fR sandbox is configured entirely through a TOML file passed via
\fBpnut --config\fR.\& This page documents every section and field.\&
.P
Fields marked with a default value are optional.\& Fields marked \fBrequired\fR must
be present when their containing section is used.\&
.P
.SH SECTIONS
.P
.SS [sandbox]
.P
General sandbox settings.\& All fields are optional.\&
.P
\fBhostname\fR (string)
.RS 4
Hostname visible inside the sandbox.\& Requires \fBnamespaces.\&uts = true\fR or
validation fails.\& Default: inherit host hostname.\&
.P
.RE
\fBcwd\fR (string)
.RS 4
Working directory for the sandboxed process.\& Default: \fB/\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBmode\fR (string)
.RS 4
Execution mode.\&
.P
\fBonce\fR
.RS 4
(default) Fork via \fBclone3\fR; parent supervises child and propagates
exit status.\&
.P
.RE
\fBexecve\fR
.RS 4
Calling process unshares and exec'\&s directly; no supervising parent.\&
.P
.RE
.RE
\fBnew_session\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Call \fBsetsid\fR(2) to create a new session and disconnect from the
controlling terminal.\& Mitigates CVE-2017-5226.\& Default: \fBtrue\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBdie_with_parent\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Set PR_SET_PDEATHSIG so the child is killed if the parent exits.\&
Default: \fBtrue\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBargv0\fR (string)
.RS 4
Override argv[0] for the command.\& Default: use the command path as
argv[0].\&
.P
.RE
\fBno_new_privs\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Set PR_SET_NO_NEW_PRIVS via \fBprctl\fR(2) before exec.\& Prevents \fBexecve\fR
from granting privileges (setuid binaries, file capabilities).\& Required
for unprivileged seccomp filter installation.\& Default: \fBtrue\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBdisable_tsc\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Disable RDTSC and RDTSCP instructions via \fBprctl\fR(2) (PR_SET_TSC).\&
x86/x86_64 only; causes SIGSEGV on RDTSC.\& Default: \fBfalse\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBdumpable\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Set PR_SET_DUMPABLE.\& When \fBfalse\fR, prevents same-UID ptrace and
\fB/proc/<pid>/mem\fR access from outside the sandbox.\& Default: \fBfalse\fR.\&
.P
.RE
.SS [namespaces]
.P
Controls which Linux namespaces are created.\& All fields are booleans.\&
.P
\fBuser\fR (bool)
.RS 4
User namespace.\& Required for unprivileged sandboxing.\& Default: \fBtrue\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBpid\fR (bool)
.RS 4
PID namespace.\& Child becomes PID 1.\& Default: \fBtrue\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBmount\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Mount namespace.\& Required for filesystem isolation via \fBpivot_root\fR(2).\&
Default: \fBtrue\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fButs\fR (bool)
.RS 4
UTS namespace.\& Required if \fBsandbox.\&hostname\fR is set.\& Default: \fBfalse\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBipc\fR (bool)
.RS 4
IPC namespace.\& Isolates System V IPC and POSIX message queues.\&
Default: \fBfalse\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBnet\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Network namespace.\& When \fBtrue\fR, the sandbox gets an isolated network stack
with only loopback.\& When \fBfalse\fR, it inherits the host network.\&
Default: \fBfalse\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBcgroup\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Cgroup namespace.\& Default: \fBfalse\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBtime\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Time namespace.\& Virtualizes CLOCK_MONOTONIC and CLOCK_BOOTTIME.\& Requires
kernel >= 5.\&6.\& Default: \fBfalse\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBallow_nested_userns\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Allow the sandboxed process to create nested user namespaces.\& When
\fBfalse\fR, seccomp rules deny \fBclone3\fR (ENOSYS), \fBclone\fR and \fBunshare\fR
with namespace flags.\& Prevents sandbox escape via namespace reshaping.\&
Default: \fBfalse\fR.\&
.P
.RE
.SS [[mount]]
.P
An ordered array of filesystem mount operations.\& Each entry is a TOML
array-of-tables element.\& Mounts are applied in order before \fBpivot_root\fR.\&
.P
Each entry must specify exactly one of: \fBbind\fR, \fBtype\fR, or \fBcontent\fR.\&
.P
\fBsrc\fR (string)
.RS 4
Source path on the host.\& Required for bind mounts.\&
.P
.RE
\fBdst\fR (string)
.RS 4
Destination path inside the sandbox.\& \fBRequired\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBbind\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Perform a recursive bind mount (MS_BIND | MS_REC).\& Default: \fBfalse\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBread_only\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Remount read-only (MS_RDONLY).\& Default: \fBfalse\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBtype\fR (string)
.RS 4
Filesystem type for a fresh mount (e.\&g.\&, \fBtmpfs\fR, \fBproc\fR, \fBmqueue\fR).\&
Mutually exclusive with \fBbind\fR and \fBcontent\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBproc_subset\fR (string)
.RS 4
Proc mount only.\& The \fBsubset=\fR mount option.\& Valid values: \fB"pid"\fR.\&
When set to \fB"pid"\fR (default), only PID-related entries are visible;
\fB/proc/sys\fR, \fB/proc/kallsyms\fR, \fB/proc/net\fR, etc.\& are hidden.\&
Set to \fBnull\fR to mount full proc.\& Requires kernel >= 5.\&8.\&
.P
.RE
\fBhidepid\fR (string)
.RS 4
Proc mount only.\& The \fBhidepid=\fR mount option.\& Valid values:
\fB"invisible"\fR (default), \fB"hidden"\fR, \fB"visible"\fR, or numeric
\fB"0"\fR, \fB"1"\fR, \fB"2"\fR.\& Controls visibility of other processes'\&
\fB/proc/<pid>\fR directories.\&
.P
.RE
\fBcontent\fR (string)
.RS 4
Inline file content.\& A regular file is created at \fBdst\fR with this content.\&
Mutually exclusive with \fBbind\fR and \fBtype\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBsize\fR (integer)
.RS 4
Size limit in bytes for \fBtmpfs\fR mounts.\& Only meaningful when
\fBtype = "tmpfs"\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBperms\fR (string)
.RS 4
Octal permission string for \fBtmpfs\fR mounts (e.\&g.\&, "0700").\& Only
meaningful when \fBtype = "tmpfs"\fR.\&
.P
.RE
.SS [uid_map]
.P
Maps a host UID range into the sandbox.\& Typically required when
\fBnamespaces.\&user = true\fR to give the sandboxed process a valid UID.\&
.P
\fBinside\fR (integer)
.RS 4
UID inside the sandbox.\& Default: \fB0\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBoutside\fR (integer)
.RS 4
Host UID to map from.\& \fBRequired\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBcount\fR (integer)
.RS 4
Number of consecutive UIDs to map.\& Default: \fB1\fR.\&
.P
.RE
.SS [gid_map]
.P
Maps a host GID range into the sandbox.\& Same schema as \fB[uid_map]\fR.\&
.P
\fBinside\fR (integer)
.RS 4
GID inside the sandbox.\& Default: \fB0\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBoutside\fR (integer)
.RS 4
Host GID to map from.\& \fBRequired\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBcount\fR (integer)
.RS 4
Number of consecutive GIDs to map.\& Default: \fB1\fR.\&
.P
.RE
.SS [env]
.P
Environment variable policy for the sandboxed process.\&
.P
\fBclear\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Clear all inherited environment variables before applying \fBset\fR and
\fBkeep\fR.\& Default: \fBfalse\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBset\fR (table)
.RS 4
Key-value pairs to set or override.\& Applied after \fBclear\fR and \fBkeep\fR.\&
.P
.nf
.RS 4
[env]
clear = true

[env\&.set]
PATH = "/usr/bin:/bin"
HOME = "/home/sandbox"
.fi
.RE
.P
.RE
\fBkeep\fR (array of strings)
.RS 4
Host environment variables to preserve when \fBclear = true\fR.\& Ignored when
\fBclear = false\fR (all variables are already inherited).\&
.P
.nf
.RS 4
[env]
clear = true
keep = ["TERM", "LANG"]
.fi
.RE
.P
.RE
.SS [rlimits]
.P
Resource limits applied via \fBsetrlimit\fR(2).\& All fields are optional; omitted
fields leave the inherited limit unchanged.\& For fields ending in \fB_mb\fR, the
value is in mebibytes and is converted to bytes internally.\&
.P
\fBnofile\fR (integer)
.RS 4
RLIMIT_NOFILE.\& Maximum number of open file descriptors.\&
.P
.RE
\fBnproc\fR (integer)
.RS 4
RLIMIT_NPROC.\& Maximum number of processes for the real user ID.\&
.P
.RE
\fBfsize_mb\fR (integer)
.RS 4
RLIMIT_FSIZE.\& Maximum file size in MiB.\&
.P
.RE
\fBstack_mb\fR (integer)
.RS 4
RLIMIT_STACK.\& Maximum stack size in MiB.\&
.P
.RE
\fBas_mb\fR (integer)
.RS 4
RLIMIT_AS.\& Maximum virtual memory (address space) in MiB.\&
.P
.RE
\fBcore_mb\fR (integer)
.RS 4
RLIMIT_CORE.\& Maximum core dump size in MiB.\&
.P
.RE
\fBcpu\fR (integer)
.RS 4
RLIMIT_CPU.\& Maximum CPU time in seconds.\&
.P
.RE
.SS [landlock]
.P
Landlock LSM filesystem access control.\& Restricts filesystem access beyond
what mount namespace isolation provides.\& All fields are arrays of path strings.\&
.P
\fBallowed_read\fR (array of strings)
.RS 4
Paths where read access is permitted.\&
.P
.RE
\fBallowed_write\fR (array of strings)
.RS 4
Paths where write access is permitted.\&
.P
.RE
\fBallowed_execute\fR (array of strings)
.RS 4
Paths where execute access is permitted.\&
.P
.RE
.SS [capabilities]
.P
Linux capability management.\& All capabilities are dropped by default.\&
.P
\fBkeep\fR (array of strings)
.RS 4
Capabilities to retain (e.\&g.\&, CAP_NET_BIND_SERVICE, CAP_SYS_PTRACE).\&
Names are validated at build time.\&
.P
.RE
.SS [fd]
.P
File descriptor policy.\&
.P
\fBclose_fds\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Close all file descriptors >= 3 that are not explicitly mapped.\&
Default: \fBtrue\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBmap\fR (array of tables)
.RS 4
Explicit FD remappings.\& Each entry has:
.P
\fBsrc\fR (integer)
.RS 4
Source file descriptor.\& \fBRequired\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBdst\fR (integer)
.RS 4
Destination file descriptor.\& \fBRequired\fR.\& Must be unique across all
mappings.\&
.P
.RE
.RE
.SS [run]
.P
Default command to execute if none is given on the command line.\& CLI arguments
(after \fB--\fR) take priority over this section.\&
.P
\fBpath\fR (string)
.RS 4
Binary path to execute.\& \fBRequired\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBargs\fR (array of strings)
.RS 4
Arguments to pass to the command.\& Default: empty.\&
.P
.RE
\fBargv0\fR (string)
.RS 4
Override argv[0] for the command.\& Overrides \fBsandbox.\&argv0\fR when the
\fB[run]\fR section command is used.\& Default: use \fBpath\fR as argv[0].\&
.P
.RE
.SS seccomp_policy, seccomp_policy_file (top-level)
.P
Seccomp-bpf syscall filtering using a Kafel-inspired DSL.\& These two fields are
mutually exclusive; specifying both is an error.\&
.P
\fBseccomp_policy\fR (string)
.RS 4
Inline seccomp policy string.\&
.P
.nf
.RS 4
seccomp_policy = """
POLICY default {
  ALLOW { read, write, exit, exit_group, brk, mmap, close }
  DENY {}
}
USE default DEFAULT KILL
"""
.fi
.RE
.P
.RE
\fBseccomp_policy_file\fR (string)
.RS 4
Path to a file containing the seccomp policy.\&
.P
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.P
A comprehensive configuration:
.P
.nf
.RS 4
[sandbox]
hostname = "box"
cwd = "/home/user"
mode = "once"
new_session = true
die_with_parent = true

[namespaces]
user = true
pid = true
mount = true
uts = true
ipc = true
net = true

[uid_map]
inside = 0
outside = 1000
count = 1

[gid_map]
inside = 0
outside = 1000
count = 1

[[mount]]
src = "/usr"
dst = "/usr"
bind = true
read_only = true

[[mount]]
dst = "/tmp"
type = "tmpfs"
size = 67108864
perms = "1777"

[[mount]]
dst = "/proc"
type = "proc"

[[mount]]
dst = "/etc/hostname"
content = "sandbox"

[env]
clear = true
keep = ["TERM", "LANG"]

[env\&.set]
PATH = "/usr/bin:/bin"
HOME = "/home/user"

[rlimits]
nofile = 256
nproc = 64
as_mb = 512

[landlock]
allowed_read = ["/usr", "/lib", "/lib64", "/etc"]
allowed_write = ["/tmp"]
allowed_execute = ["/usr/bin", "/bin"]

[capabilities]
keep = []

[fd]
close_fds = true

[run]
path = "/bin/sh"
args = ["-i"]
.fi
.RE
.P
.SH SEE ALSO
.P
\fBpnut\fR(1), \fBtoml\fR(5), \fBsetrlimit\fR(2), \fBseccomp\fR(2), \fBlandlock\fR(7),
\fBcapabilities\fR(7)
